This paper addresses the issue of including potential trends
of economic development and environmental awareness in
climate impact research. The study aims to provide a sound
scientiﬁc basis for the development of pan-European man-
agement recommendations for coastal areas. We therefore
assessed and compared the effects of climate change on
water availability and nutrient loads under various land use
and management settings in the catchments of four Eur-
